featured_reviews.review_translated_text: This large Hanuman shrine in Chennoor, Manchiryala district is opposite the Brahmin Wada on the way from Sathya Sai Seva Samiti towards Ravi Chettu Centre. Locals also call this temple as the height of Hanumandla Gudi. Although the Hanuman temple is big in name, the idol is not that big. But the temple was built at some height from the ground. Sitaram idols are placed in one corner of this. With this, the lack of a Ram temple in Chennuru has been solved to some extent. Crowd of devotees is normal.
